HEADWORD: Senary
<hw>Sen"a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>senarius</ets>, fr. <ets>seni</ets> six each, fr. <ets>sex</ets>
six. See <er>Six</er>.]</ety> <def>Of six; belonging to six; containing
six.</def> <rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
